      "stem": "Solve: \\(\\log_3(2x + 1) = 2\\)",
      "stemBn": "সমাধান করো: \\(\\log_3(2x + 1) = 2\\)",
      "parts": [
        {
          "l": "ক",
          "m": 2,
          "q": "Convert the equation from logarithmic to exponential form.",
          "sol": [
            {
              "m": "\\log_3(2x+1) = 2 \\implies 2x + 1 = 3^2 = \\boxed{9}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "l": "খ",
          "m": 4,
          "q": "Find the value of \\(x\\).",
          "sol": [
            {
              "m": "2x + 1 = 9"
            },
            {
              "m": "2x = 8 \\implies x = \\boxed{4}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "l": "গ",
          "m": 4,
          "q": "Verify the answer and find \\(\\log_3(4x + 1)\\).",
          "sol": [
            {
              "t": "Verification: \\(\\log_3(2(4)+1) = \\log_3 9 = 2\\) ✓"
            },
            {
              "m": "\\log_3(4(4)+1) = \\log_3 17"
            },
            {
              "t": "Since \\(3^2 = 9\\) and \\(3^3 = 27\\), we know \\(2 < \\log_3 17 < 3\\)."
            },
            {
              "m": "\\log_3 17 = \\frac{\\log 17}{\\log 3} = \\frac{1.2304}{0.4771} \\approx \\boxed{2.579}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
